<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1913-09-24T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1913-09-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="1457" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1457">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 819.55/25.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Chargé
                                    d’Affaires</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegrams.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Panama</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-09-24">
                                    <hi rend="italic">September 24, 1913</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>My appointment in charge of Chinese interests in Panama favorably
                            received by Government and press. The Minister for Foreign Affairs has
                            announced postponement of the application of Law 50 giving time for its
                            full consideration. Fourteen hundred Chinese cédulas today deposited
                            with the Legation for examination and safekeeping. Kindly forward
                            assurance of my appreciation and earnest efforts to the Chinese Minister
                            for Foreign Affairs.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Wicker.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>